Still smiling from all the fun I had at the Colorado Trombone Festival 2023. It was my first recital on my new model with @theinbrass.official and the resonance this instrument gets is unreal! A big THANK YOU to  Sondra Bell for having me out and a to my favorite pianist, Michael Schneider, for lending his incredible musicianship and bringing each piece to life with me 😊

MAY GUEST ARTISTS!!!!

A Slide School FIRST! We are proud to bring back previous Slide School member, Eden Garza, to talk about his tenure process in the Seattle Symphony and the techniques he used in the practice room to get him there!

We've also got the incredible Joseph Rodriguez joining us to talk about his illustrious career in the Cincinnati Symphony and about their upcoming bass trombone vacancy. An incredible musician, human being and teacher. This class is not to be missed!!

Ready for my first event of the week at Blast of Brass!! @theslideschool @theinbrass.official @griegomouthpieces

What a BLAST! This week was a very special one for me. I had the true pleasure and honor of sharing the stage with Texas legends Keith Meek (@meekkeith ), Jimmy Clark and carrying the torch for Jimmy and the great Neill Humfeld, Megan Boutin (@megan_boutin_trombone ), the newly appointed trombone professor at Texas A&M - Commerce. It was inspiring getting to work with all the students at Blast of Brass and see them grow, ask great questions, learn and perform at a true Texas-high level on the final concert. Keith, thank you for having me as your Featured Artist this year. It’s truly an event I will remember for the rest of my career!!
